cKyKG2lMLgrn-XLlYu9iVGM_tBZBz8t5HcIH7h9jX7VfL-EOQPRPJae1T8yE3b2KEwDMheeKdeID6w2776cgcJUGvoC9zUUcbfjFf_TCLXvCZf2J0Odp-HInk51k67VFc7SRU1_p7EPCo4iipvv-ilTIxu73Ku1gyfn1skiipc_jGltjKUyJ0kvaifabyFAqZ7GjCmfxYYTNU-ZMGz8AUzVqFLEt0ZDcWoDxg-BTu1xLFUyIbXhGzpJhA6JI2NhgJUlAQSyWLwkjSjG5_f-4vh5GACMMMnNU6YU97DADLwHnN9lh2Q2yZCKSLRNKhvqz6BMYp4dWB45yNKQjUc7PiU7WoOxBlJIKoTnjl_MjKY3mpvXIM77Jy89kM=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating HTTP request coverage**\\n\\nTo cover HTTP request execution meaningfully, I'd typically need a local endpoint, and MockWebServer is the official test dependency for that. If I don't have it, I could use JDK HttpServer for HTTP/1.1, but I'm curious about HTTPS or HTTP2 options. It seems like meaningful coverage could come from using public API builders and a local server. However, I’m thinking the generator doesn't strictly require an extra dependency for adequate coverage.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying generated tests**\\n\\nI'm thinking about what it means when I say \\\"generated tests must set,\\\" particularly regarding whether these tests exercise okhttp3.internal.Util, which I see that they do. I have to point out that it seems like \\\"native must set -H:+AddAllCharsets\\\" comes from a meticulous process, but I’m not entirely sure if that’s solid research. I should pin down what this all means to avoid any confusion!\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"advisory_preparation\",\n  \"summary\": \"No extra Maven dependency or Docker image is needed; OkHttp 3.8.1 is self-contained apart from transitive Okio, but meaningful native coverage should preserve the known charset/platform test setup.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"Set the GraalVM Native test build argument `-H:+AddAllCharsets` when tests exercise `okhttp3.internal.Util` or code paths that load it, because OkHttp 3.8.1 initializes UTF-32 charsets statically. For optional platform reachability coverage, keep tests self-contained with source-level stubs for Android and Jetty ALPN classes that OkHttp discovers reflectively rather than adding real Android or ALPN artifacts. Use the 3.8.x `Util.intersect(Util.NATURAL_ORDER, first, second)` signature if updating the existing compile-failing test.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Adding real Android or Jetty ALPN dependencies could change `Platform.get()` detection and make tests brittle.\",\n    \"Without `-H:+AddAllCharsets`, JVM compilation may pass while native-image verification can fail on charset initialization.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_062e1c3b1a667236016a3eb0a0a80c81948528f003ee609979\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 8245, "output": 1729, "cacheRead": 24064, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 34038, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782493325604, "responseId": "resp_062e1c3b1a667236016a3eb08e0fe8819491a1e6fcf04e56c3"}, "toolResults": []}
